126
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:34,440
Who knows? Anything could happen.

127
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:35,550
Yeah, you're right.

128
00:03:35,550 --> 00:03:35,960
Totally.

129
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,270
(Too good)
It could happen.

130
00:03:39,470 --> 00:03:40,830
Well, let's go through the options.

131
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:41,670
First,

132
00:03:42,530 --> 00:03:43,240
I go to Hangzhou.

133
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,630
Come join me in an online business.

134
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:46,570
What would I do?

135
00:03:46,570 --> 00:03:47,440
"3, 2, 1, link's up!"

136
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:48,710
That's definitely not your thing.

137
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:49,080
Then...

138
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:49,990
If you really want in,

139
00:03:49,990 --> 00:03:51,830
I could take some nice photos for you

140
00:03:51,830 --> 00:03:53,720
and you could start your own account.

141
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:55,110
You think I can pull this off?

142
00:03:55,670 --> 00:03:56,240
Maybe.

143
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:56,960
Maybe you can.

144
00:03:57,360 --> 00:03:58,550
They're tired of it.

145
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,990
Those two are glued together.

146
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:01,080
It's so annoying.

147
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,670
And they never have anything new to say.

148
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:05,890
When the audience sees this,

149
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:07,510
they're like, did we watch this yesterday?

150
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,160
Didn't they say the same thing yesterday?

151
00:04:11,630 --> 00:04:12,910
Here they go again, repeating it.

152
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,440
It's fine. If they don't ship us, I do.

153
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:26,600
Nope.

154
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,380
(He takes back a candy.)

155
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:29,600
Come on, give me one.

156
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,420
(Feeds it over.)

157
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:35,790
Where's the ice?

158
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:36,110
Ice?

159
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:36,830
Ice.

160
00:04:36,830 --> 00:04:37,510
Where is the ice?

161
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:38,000
Ice cube.

162
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,670
I'm sitting out today.

163
00:04:39,670 --> 00:04:40,440
Why?

164
00:04:40,440 --> 00:04:41,040
He's weak.

165
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:41,480
I...

166
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,790
My liver's crying for mercy.

167
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:44,790
(Mercy)
It's begging me to stop torturing it.

168
00:04:44,790 --> 00:04:46,350
But that'll help you keep your figure.

169
00:04:46,350 --> 00:04:47,390
It's turning into one-pack.

170
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:48,110
Didn't you see?

171
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:49,830
Let me.

172
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:51,000
One-pack.

173
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,880
Uh-oh.

174
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,720
He's doomed.

175
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,600
Is he?

176
00:04:56,070 --> 00:04:57,550
After watching you two closely,

177
00:04:57,550 --> 00:04:59,760
I actually think you make a good match.

178
00:04:59,760 --> 00:04:59,950
Why?

179
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:00,600
Tianyu.

180
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:00,830
Yeah.

181
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:01,100
Why?

182
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:01,990
(Go ahead)
Everything.

183
00:05:01,990 --> 00:05:02,550
Height.

184
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:03,830
And then personality.

185
00:05:04,550 --> 00:05:05,760
What's so funny?

186
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,920
(Dark skin, light skin)
One's darker, one's lighter.

187
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:08,320
From

188
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,110
the looks.

189
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:11,160
Don't you think so?

190
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:11,880
What the heck?

191
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,200
It's that kind of...

192
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,760
unexpected match.

193
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:15,950
One dark, one light.

194
00:05:15,950 --> 00:05:17,160
Yeah, that's exactly...

195
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:18,670
A palm and back combo.

196
00:05:18,670 --> 00:05:20,480
You've never played that Palm or Back?

197
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,550
Which boy and girl match?

198
00:05:23,340 --> 00:05:25,620
(Takes a sip of juice)

199
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,440
I just spit on it.

200
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:29,830
Tastes good.

201
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:32,510
He loves it.

202
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,320
We're like elementary school kids every day.

203
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,480
That's exactly the vibe.

204
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,070
The kind of vibe that couples have.

205
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,510
Who's the oldest among you?

206
00:05:40,270 --> 00:05:41,070
Me?

207
00:05:41,070 --> 00:05:42,110
I was born in 2002.

208
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,040
(23 years old)
Not old.

209
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:43,720
She's younger.

210
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:45,270
(22 years old)

211
00:05:45,270 --> 00:05:45,930
What about you?

212
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,440
(Don't start)
I'm the oldest.

213
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,110
Yeah, you are.

214
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,320
I'm the oldest.

215
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:50,640
Crazy.

216
00:05:51,410 --> 00:05:52,200
I'm not the oldest.

217
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:52,920
Charlie is.

218
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,640
Yeah, it's me.

219
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,820
(34 years old)

220
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:55,670
Uncle.

221
00:05:55,670 --> 00:05:56,480
How are you feeling?

222
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,760
Uncle Charlie.

223
00:05:58,760 --> 00:05:59,450
(The only uncle)

224
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:00,390
So I fractured my bone.

225
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:01,330
Getting old, you know.

226
00:06:02,350 --> 00:06:04,550
Osteoporosis.

227
00:06:04,580 --> 00:06:05,860
(Take care)
Take some calcium.

228
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:07,640
Thanks, I appreciate it.

229
00:06:09,790 --> 00:06:10,580
Take some calcium.

230
00:06:10,830 --> 00:06:11,480
Pass it over.

231
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:14,670
Cheers.

232
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,180
(DAY 10)

233
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:22,530
(Yang and Enda,
ready for date)

234
00:06:22,530 --> 00:06:23,510
Did you sleep well?

235
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:24,320
Slept like a baby.

236
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,070
Did you miss me?

237
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,200
Of course.

238
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:26,670
Really?

239
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:27,110
You've been

240
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:29,420
lingering in my mind.

241
00:06:29,420 --> 00:06:30,600
Yang.
[*as sheep in Chinese]

242
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,760
One sheep, two sheep, three...

243
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,140
Sounds like you're busy.

244
00:06:36,140 --> 00:06:36,840
Got a date later.

245
00:06:37,270 --> 00:06:37,790
Happy?

246
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:38,320
Yeah, I am.

247
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,990
Seeing you already makes me happy.

248
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:42,200
Same here.

249
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:43,640
Let's go.

250
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:48,590
Do I look better with straight or curly hair?

251
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,670
They give different vibes.

252
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,040
Curly feels a bit more girly.

253
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,580
(observing)

254
00:06:55,580 --> 00:06:57,980
(Hands on the wheel, safety first.)

255
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:00,220
(Love is precious, but life matters more.)

256
00:07:00,230 --> 00:07:01,390
This promise really...

257
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:02,880
