258
00:07:03,230 --> 00:07:04,000
Why do you say that?

259
00:07:04,510 --> 00:07:06,110
"We've been together for seven years,

260
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:09,720
trying to find who we used to be."

261
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,230
So you think...

262
00:07:11,230 --> 00:07:12,760
we can be together for seven years.

263
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:13,350
Right?

264
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:15,510
How about seventy years?

265
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:18,350
Seven years feels a bit too short.

266
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,880
After 7 years, would we still do

267
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:35,000
things like this?

268
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,510
Of course.

269
00:07:36,510 --> 00:07:37,070
Definitely.

270
00:07:39,830 --> 00:07:41,290
I could hold your hand for 70 years.

271
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,920
I once read something interesting.

272
00:07:50,550 --> 00:07:51,230
It said that

273
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,480
after seven years pass,

274
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:54,880
the way you treat

275
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,760
the person you love

276
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,440
becomes like how you

277
00:07:58,440 --> 00:07:59,320
treat your hands.

278
00:08:00,110 --> 00:08:01,170
You barely feel anything.

279
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,760
But once it's gone,

280
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,770
you can't accept it.

281
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,950
Then try your best

282
00:08:06,950 --> 00:08:08,720
not to get yourself hurt, okay?

283
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:10,610
(Don't hurt your hand)

284
00:08:10,610 --> 00:08:11,390
Sure.

285
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:11,950
I promise you.

286
00:08:13,790 --> 00:08:14,440
Look,

287
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:17,060
(Little White)

288
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:18,160
You actually brought our

289
00:08:18,550 --> 00:08:19,580
Little White out with you.

290
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,900
(First date)
Let's call it Little White.

291
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,420
It makes me think of you.

292
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:25,260
(Token of our love)

293
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,820
I don't want to take it off.

294
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:27,790
Why not?

295
00:08:27,790 --> 00:08:28,880
Because it has a name.

296
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:30,380
(Name of the date spot)

297
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:33,200
Where we had our first date.

298
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:33,760
Yeah.

299
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:35,520
I left it on purpose.

300
00:08:36,590 --> 00:08:37,670
So cute.

301
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,640
Seriously, it's adorable.

302
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,590
The weather's perfect today.

303
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:48,320
This whole day feels so romantic.

304
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,000
Life on the island has been really nice.

305
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,400
Every day is just like

306
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:54,960
living inside this pink bubble.

307
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:57,000
So when we leave the island

308
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,030
and go back to real life,

309
00:08:59,030 --> 00:09:00,550
aren't you a little scared that

310
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:02,200
the bubble might burst?

311
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:02,760
And then,

312
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,960
you realize some promises

313
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,320
aren't that easy to keep.

314
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:08,160
How would we handle that?

315
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:09,630
It could happen.

316
00:09:09,630 --> 00:09:10,590
Let's talk about it.

317
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:11,640
Honestly...

318
00:09:13,550 --> 00:09:15,590
So in the end, the real issue is still

319
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:16,710
the distance between us.

320
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:18,910
It's the biggest problem.

321
00:09:18,910 --> 00:09:21,780
(The problem of distance
is hard to overcome.)

322
00:09:21,790 --> 00:09:22,550
How do we deal with

323
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,030
the distance?

324
00:09:25,710 --> 00:09:26,910
If I move to Hangzhou for you,

325
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:27,910
what job could I do?

326
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,550
If you were to a job in Hangzhou...

327
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:32,980
you're lowering your standards for me.

328
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,320
I don't like that.

329
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:37,230
You've got such a bright future ahead,

330
00:09:37,590 --> 00:09:39,030
yet you'd be choosing another path,

331
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:40,540
starting all over again from nothing.

332
00:09:40,540 --> 00:09:41,840
I think that's...

333
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,400
unfair.

334
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:45,580
(Giving up a stable life for someone
doesn't solve the problem.)

335
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:47,760
Then if I move to your city,

336
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,670
what could I do there?

337
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:50,350
Model.

338
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,540
Model?

339
00:09:52,150 --> 00:09:53,590
Not many tall people in Singapore.

340
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:56,520
So you must be the most suitable one.

341
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,550
I don't speak the language.

342
00:09:58,550 --> 00:09:59,470
I can teach you.

343
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,350
Teach me now.

344
00:10:02,450 --> 00:10:03,490
What do you want to learn?

345
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:04,940
The sun is beautiful,

346
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,520
but not as beautiful as you.

347
00:10:07,790 --> 00:10:10,150
Stop saying things like that to me every day.

348
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,000
I can't handle it.

349
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,790
Teach me.

350
00:10:12,590 --> 00:10:13,200
No idea.

351
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:13,840
I don't know.

352
00:10:14,590 --> 00:10:15,640
Then how can you teach me?

353
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,670
We can start with everyday phrases.

354
00:10:17,670 --> 00:10:18,640
Like, I want to eat.

355
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:20,080
I want to order food.

356
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:20,910
I want this one.

357
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:22,200
But I know how.

358
00:10:24,910 --> 00:10:26,590
You see, every time we talk,

359
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,400
we never actually try to

360
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,640
to tackle this issue.

361
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:31,320
We always switch topics somehow.

362
00:10:31,710 --> 00:10:34,030
But the truth is,
it's hard to fix in real life.

363
00:10:34,030 --> 00:10:34,840
Yeah, exactly.

364
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:36,150
So why not just enjoy this moment?

365
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:37,350
Enjoy this moment of pure calm,

366
00:10:37,350 --> 00:10:39,150
the sunlight, the sea breeze, the beach.

367
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:43,320
Feel the ocean breeze.

368
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:43,960
It's relaxing.

369
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,110
When you're with me,

370
00:10:46,110 --> 00:10:47,320
have you ever thought

371
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,450
that part of this is acting?

372
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:50,470
Acting?

373
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:52,470
I mean,

374
00:10:52,470 --> 00:10:54,030
it's because people are watching us?

375
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:54,440
Or maybe…

376
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:54,960
No.

377
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,790
There are cameras.

378
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:56,640
If

379
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,080
it's about acting,

380
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:01,350
why would I make myself look so pathetic?

381
00:11:02,110 --> 00:11:02,690
Pathetic? How?

382
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:03,840
I mean,

383
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,400
why does it have to end up

384
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,230
with such a huge problem

385
00:11:07,230 --> 00:11:08,100
right in front of me,

386
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:09,550
making me feel this awful?

387
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:11,760
Do you ever regret it?

388
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,280
No, I don't.

389
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:14,470
I'd still make

390
00:11:14,470 --> 00:11:16,200
the same choice no matter what.

391
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:18,200
What if the one you liked was

392
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,640
Yijia or Jiayi?

393
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:20,470
But

394
00:11:20,470 --> 00:11:21,790
I never liked them.

395
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:23,230
It's always you.

396
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:25,550
So what now?

397
00:11:28,710 --> 00:11:30,000
You like it

398
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,110
when there's some challenge.

399
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:33,350
Yeah.

400
00:11:33,350 --> 00:11:34,440
I guess I like hardship.

401
00:11:35,490 --> 00:11:37,200
It makes the relationship feel worthwhile.

402
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,590
You're talking big here.

403
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,190
I want the bittersweet part of love.

404
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:45,470
No way.

405
00:11:45,470 --> 00:11:46,710
Love won't let you suffer.

406
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:49,550
Isn't long distance love's hardship?

407
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,310
(If long distance)

408
00:11:52,310 --> 00:11:54,970
(can finally leads us somewhere,)

409
00:11:54,970 --> 00:11:57,110
(then that waiting process is actually)

410
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,170
(worth it.)

411
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:06,980
I'm heading down first.

412
00:12:11,110 --> 00:12:12,400
Wait a sec.

413
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:18,110
I want to kiss you.

414
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:22,080
Did they see us?

415
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,400
Pretty sure they did.

416
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:37,660
(Yan & Guan's date at Malt Cave Restaurant)

417
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:44,760
Honey.

418
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:45,350
Babe.

419
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:48,110
I set this up.

420
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:01,690
Which one is your favorite?

421
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:02,760
That one.

422
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:05,110
The one at the stadium.

423
00:13:05,710 --> 00:13:06,790
I was sitting next to you.

424
00:13:07,350 --> 00:13:07,760
And you?

425
00:13:08,550 --> 00:13:09,400
The one on the top.

426
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:10,320
We were

427
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,230
in the supermarket.

428
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:19,400
Thank you, babe.

429
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:22,960
You're welcome, honey.

430
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:27,790
Can I ask you something?

431
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:30,030
How long do you think people should date

432
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:30,960
before getting married?

433
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,880
Ideally, for me,

434
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:34,880
around thirty.

435
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:35,520
Same here.

436
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,320
Twenty‑eight.

437
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:38,940
(Innocent look)

438
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:39,400
How old?

439
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:40,590
Twenty-eight.

440
00:13:41,670 --> 00:13:42,200
Oh.

441
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:42,960
(Didn't catch that)

442
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,280
You think how old? Eighteen?

443
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,350
I thought thirty-eight.

444
00:13:48,110 --> 00:13:50,590
How do you think
our married life is going today?

445
00:13:51,470 --> 00:13:52,320
I think it's great.

446
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,470
Aren't you happy though?

447
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:55,400
I'm really happy.

448
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,080
I'm super happy, actually.

449
00:13:59,470 --> 00:14:00,440
Let me check the photos.

450
00:14:05,230 --> 00:14:06,160
Do you have anything

451
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:06,910
on your mind?

452
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:07,960
Our life on the island

453
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,440
is about to come to an end.

454
00:14:10,030 --> 00:14:11,520
My thought is life there is ending.

455
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:12,960
But we're not ending yet.

456
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:14,840
Well, of course we're not.

457
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:15,640
Yeah.

458
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:17,400
But what I mean is,

459
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,450
have you learned anything

460
00:14:18,450 --> 00:14:19,350
on the Balance Island?

461
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:22,470
I've learned how to talk to people.

462
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:23,590
And then,

463
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:25,440
how to survive on a deserted island.

464
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,230
Survive? How?

465
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:27,350
Instant noodles.

466
00:14:28,280 --> 00:14:29,380
Living off instant noodles.

467
00:14:29,380 --> 00:14:30,200
And eggs.

468
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,440
Every day it's just noodles and eggs.

469
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:36,500
(Picks up the photo again)

470
00:14:37,790 --> 00:14:38,890
Do you have a favorite one?

471
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:40,840
You look so cheerful here.

472
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:41,520
Of course I do.

473
00:14:41,520 --> 00:14:42,550
Is it the first day?

474
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:43,400
Yeah.

475
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:45,400
(First meeting)
I'm Zhu Huiyan.

476
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,790
You can call me Yan.

477
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:48,790
Yan.

478
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:50,080
I'm Wu Guanjie.

479
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:53,080
Guan.

480
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,230
It sounds cute.

481
00:14:59,110 --> 00:15:00,390
We took so many photos that day.

482
00:15:00,710 --> 00:15:01,030
Yeah.

483
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:03,640
I think the shots here turned out amazing.

484
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,470
What do you think?

485
00:15:04,470 --> 00:15:05,200
You look amazing.

486
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:05,670
Me? No.

487
00:15:05,670 --> 00:15:06,500
You look great too.

488
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:11,520
That was the day by the river.

489
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,110
Do you think my cheers that day...

490
00:15:13,110 --> 00:15:14,230
...actually gave you a boost?

491
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:16,030
Yeah, they did.

492
00:15:16,030 --> 00:15:17,320
You were shouting really loud.

493
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,280
Of course.

494
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:19,450
Almost yelling my lungs out.

495
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:21,710
Go, Guan!

496
00:15:21,710 --> 00:15:23,000
Come on, Guan!

497
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:25,400
Come on, Guan, you got this!

498
00:15:30,110 --> 00:15:31,000
That was awesome!

499
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,150
That day was pretty fun.

500
00:15:32,150 --> 00:15:33,470
You mean that game, right?

501
00:15:33,470 --> 00:15:33,840
Yeah.

502
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,440
Everyone

503
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,200
gave it their all

504
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,470
just to win that championship.

505
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:39,150
Yeah, totally.

506
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:41,150
My legs almost gave out.

507
00:15:43,030 --> 00:15:43,440
Same here.

508
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:44,960
My body ached so much that day.

509
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:47,470
Sit on my right side.

510
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:48,710
Why?

511
00:15:49,350 --> 00:15:50,320
I just want you to.

512
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,230
Come sit over here.

513
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:59,000
Alright, sit here.

514
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:01,200
Is it because it makes you

515
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,230
feel more secure, right?

516
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:05,790
Are you happy?

517
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:06,760
Yes.

518
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:09,230
The level of your happiness,

519
00:16:09,230 --> 00:16:10,080
one to a hundred.

520
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:10,520
A hundred.

521
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:12,100
A hundred and one.

522
00:16:12,320 --> 00:16:13,590
Then I'll give a hundred and ten.

523
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,030
Higher than mine anyway.

524
00:16:15,030 --> 00:16:15,710
Of course.

525
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:16,790
Competitive much.

526
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:20,760
Honey.

527
00:16:21,710 --> 00:16:22,640
Why so sudden?

528
00:16:23,030 --> 00:16:23,880
I haven't finished it.

529
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:27,620
There's plenty over there.

530
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:29,840
Let's take that home to eat.

531
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:30,640
Honey.

532
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:31,470
Okay.

533
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:34,030
You hardly ever feed me yourself.

534
00:16:34,370 --> 00:16:35,490
What's gotten into you today?

535
00:16:36,470 --> 00:16:37,670
Because we just got married.

536
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:38,400
Honey.

537
00:16:39,230 --> 00:16:40,280
From now on...

538
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:41,960
Every single day,

539
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,150
I'll feed you myself.

540
00:16:43,150 --> 00:16:43,710
Honey.

541
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:45,280
Honey.

542
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:46,350
Are you sleepy?

543
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:47,400
I'm full now.

544
00:16:47,400 --> 00:16:47,880
Honey.

545
00:16:48,910 --> 00:16:49,760
Why do you...

546
00:16:52,790 --> 00:16:53,640
add "honey"

547
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,710
after every sentence?

548
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:56,200
Right, honey.

549
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,200
Just say it once.

550
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,300
Once when we meet is enough.

551
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,620
You don't have to keep saying...

552
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:01,000
But I like calling you honey.

553
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:01,910
Then as you wish.

554
00:17:04,830 --> 00:17:06,230
Why did you buy me pink roses?

555
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:06,800
Honey.

556
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:09,280
It suits the way you look today.

557
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:09,950
Oh?

558
00:17:09,950 --> 00:17:10,920
You're not wearing red.

559
00:17:13,350 --> 00:17:14,110
Do you like it?

560
00:17:14,110 --> 00:17:14,640
I do.

561
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,800
Can you give me a bouquet every day?

562
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,680
That might be a bit hard.

563
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:20,190
Why is that, honey?

564
00:17:20,190 --> 00:17:21,640
Because we only do that on special

565
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,650
(Unhappy)
days.

566
00:17:22,830 --> 00:17:23,330
Could you...

567
00:17:23,330 --> 00:17:23,930
Or anniversary.

568
00:17:23,930 --> 00:17:25,190
...give me a bouquet each day.

569
00:17:25,190 --> 00:17:26,310
Honey.

570
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:27,800
I'll pick some for you.

571
00:17:28,230 --> 00:17:29,290
(Changes her mind)
Sure.

572
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:34,920
I feel like going out.

573
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:35,520
Okay.

574
00:17:40,070 --> 00:17:41,760
Honey.

575
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:42,560
What is it?

576
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:43,830
What's wrong?

577
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,040
I'm so happy.

578
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:45,760
Honey.

579
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:46,680
How happy?

580
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:47,310
Super happy.

581
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:48,830
I'm smiling so hard right now.

582
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,790
That you can't close your mouth.

583
00:17:51,350 --> 00:17:52,230
Can't stop smiling.

584
00:17:52,230 --> 00:17:52,800
Yeah, totally.

585
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,350
I just can't stop grinning.

586
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:58,160
Do you usually drink milk tea?

587
00:17:58,760 --> 00:17:59,280
Neither do I.

588
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,520
What a coincidence, babe.

589
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:02,710
We'd have so much in common.

590
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:03,840
That's why we ended up being

591
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,230
a married couple.

592
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:09,680
Look.

593
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:10,590
It's so beautiful.

594
00:18:11,310 --> 00:18:12,680
This is unbelievably romantic.

595
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:19,760
If I weren't right next to you,

596
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:20,560
will you miss me?

597
00:18:21,190 --> 00:18:21,680
Yeah,

598
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:22,230
I really will.

599
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:23,070
How much?

600
00:18:24,710 --> 00:18:25,560
A lot.

601
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:28,760
This feels so chill.

602
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:29,560
I feel the same.

603
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:31,680
I don't want to leave.

604
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:32,350
I think

605
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:33,160
we should stay here.

606
00:18:33,710 --> 00:18:34,590
Feel the sea breeze.

607
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:35,470
Listen to some music.

608
00:18:35,470 --> 00:18:36,710
With someone you like.

609
00:18:38,110 --> 00:18:38,950
That's real peace.

610
00:18:43,430 --> 00:18:44,830
Everyone would be so jealous.

611
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:46,310
I think so too.

612
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:52,620
(Departing, return to the island)

613
00:18:54,430 --> 00:18:56,160
What do you think they'll do today?

614
00:18:56,450 --> 00:18:57,990
We're shooting our wedding dress photos.

615
00:18:57,990 --> 00:18:59,560
I really can't guess what they'll do.

616
00:19:00,350 --> 00:19:01,790
Will they get their marriage license?

617
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:03,350
(Just a wild guess)

618
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:04,040
Then?

619
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,110
Take a guess.

620
00:19:07,110 --> 00:19:08,000
I think...

621
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,000
You think...

622
00:19:09,710 --> 00:19:11,470
Maybe doing some crafts.

623
00:19:12,070 --> 00:19:13,070
Crafts?

624
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:15,590
Do you like making crafts?

625
00:19:17,010 --> 00:19:17,990
Depends on who I'm with.

626
00:19:18,310 --> 00:19:19,040
What if it's me?

627
00:19:19,710 --> 00:19:20,950
If it's you, sure.

628
00:19:20,950 --> 00:19:22,100
We can make crafts together.

629
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,520
Yeah, let's do that.

630
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,270
If it's someone else,

631
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:26,560
no?

632
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:27,930
Not with anyone else.

633
00:19:28,660 --> 00:19:30,660
(Satisfied)

634
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:35,400
Where do you feel happiest?

635
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,040
Honey.

636
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:37,310
Taking photos.

637
00:19:38,160 --> 00:19:38,800
What kind?

638
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:39,400
Wedding photos.

639
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,280
Because I've never

640
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:42,230
taken anything like that before.

641
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:43,110
Wedding photos?

642
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:44,160
A photo shoot?

643
00:19:44,160 --> 00:19:45,920
Not wedding photos.

644
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:46,950
I mean photo shoot.

645
00:19:46,950 --> 00:19:48,190
You've never done a photo shoot?

646
00:19:48,190 --> 00:19:48,760
Yeah.

647
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:50,390
No wonder you're so awkward

648
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:51,310
in front of the camera.

649
00:19:52,190 --> 00:19:53,640
What do you think we'll do tomorrow?

650
00:19:54,310 --> 00:19:55,040
Will there...

651
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:57,920
be a confession balloon?

652
00:19:58,470 --> 00:19:59,590
A confession balloon?

653
00:19:59,590 --> 00:20:00,710
What do you think?

654
00:20:01,190 --> 00:20:01,560
Who?

655
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,530
Who's confessing to you?

656
00:20:02,830 --> 00:20:03,640
What?

657
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:04,920
(Playing dumb)
Who else?

658
00:20:05,590 --> 00:20:07,160
Is there a new male guest coming?

659
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:07,680
Really?

660
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:08,210
No idea.

661
00:20:08,210 --> 00:20:09,160
Who's confessing to you?

662
00:20:10,220 --> 00:20:12,100
(Glares intensely)

663
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:12,920
I'll toss you out.

664
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:16,230
What do you mean?

665
00:20:16,230 --> 00:20:16,950
Not you?

666
00:20:16,950 --> 00:20:17,360
Nope.

667
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:18,430
(Think before you speak)
Then...

668
00:20:18,430 --> 00:20:19,110
So, you want it?

669
00:20:19,470 --> 00:20:20,350
Of course I do.

670
00:20:20,350 --> 00:20:20,830
You do?

671
00:20:21,070 --> 00:20:21,520
No way.

672
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:24,400
What's that supposed to mean?

673
00:20:24,710 --> 00:20:25,110
Nothing.

674
00:20:25,110 --> 00:20:25,690
Just kidding.

675
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:30,280
Honey.

676
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:32,040
What's wrong?

677
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:34,110
I might not

678
00:20:34,830 --> 00:20:36,350
get to call you that later, right?

679
00:20:37,230 --> 00:20:37,760
No way.

680
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:39,070
You can call me whenever you want.

681
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:41,400
When you're angry me,

682
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:42,760
do you change the way

683
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:44,040
you call me?

684
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:45,430
I just ignore you.

685
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:46,710
Like this.

686
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:49,400
And what do you call me?

687
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:50,160
Wu Guanjie.

688
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,420
(Full name means trouble.)

689
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:53,190
Do you think I've been angry?

690
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,160
You're angry every single day.

691
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:55,950
No way, really?

692
00:20:55,950 --> 00:20:56,430
Yeah.

693
00:20:56,430 --> 00:20:57,450
Why don't you cheer me up?

694
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,590
Because the more I do, the worse it gets.

695
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:00,920
Why is that?

696
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:02,560
Cheer me up, then I won't stay mad.

697
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,040
Really?

698
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:03,350
Really.

699
00:21:03,350 --> 00:21:04,710
Cheer me up and everything's fine.

700
00:21:04,860 --> 00:21:07,660
(Yan's actually easy to please.)

701
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,040
Got it, honey?

702
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:12,880
Got it.

703
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,520
Time goes by so fast.

704
00:21:17,950 --> 00:21:20,040
Feels like I've been here for about...

705
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:21,830
a week, give or take.

706
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,230
You came on the

707
00:21:23,230 --> 00:21:24,830
third day to the island, right?

708
00:21:24,830 --> 00:21:25,110
Second.

709
00:21:25,110 --> 00:21:25,560
Second day.

710
00:21:26,070 --> 00:21:27,310
That's when you met me.

711
00:21:27,310 --> 00:21:27,590
Yeah.

712
00:21:27,590 --> 00:21:28,860
Next day, we went to the island.

713
00:21:28,860 --> 00:21:29,160
Yeah.

714
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:31,590
Time really flies.

715
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:32,160
Yeah.

716
00:21:33,470 --> 00:21:33,760
No way.

717
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:34,750
I just wanted to ask you

718
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,390
that deep question I asked earlier today.

719
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:39,350
If, say, that purple shell wasn't me,

720
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:41,010
but you saw me on the island,

721
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:43,190
would you change your choice?

722
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:45,190
Actually,

723
00:21:45,190 --> 00:21:46,100
I'm not really the type

724
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:48,230
to make the first move

725
00:21:48,230 --> 00:21:49,400
or start a conversation.

726
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,190
Why not?

727
00:21:50,190 --> 00:21:51,950
Because I'm honestly just not

728
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:52,920
a very forward person.

729
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:54,350
I tend to rely more

730
00:21:55,070 --> 00:21:57,470
on attraction than action.

731
00:21:57,470 --> 00:21:58,880
Then we are actually quite alike.

732
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:00,160
Not really.

733
00:22:00,470 --> 00:22:01,310
How not?

734
00:22:01,310 --> 00:22:01,880
Just not.

735
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:03,280
I'm a bit cuter.

736
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,830
You're not as cute as me.

737
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:05,830
Right.

738
00:22:05,830 --> 00:22:06,590
You're the cutest,

739
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:07,040
babe.

740
00:22:07,830 --> 00:22:08,760
Love you, hubby.

741
00:22:19,050 --> 00:22:20,830
(Charlie & Liu Jiayi)
I love amusement parks.

742
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:22,950
Yeah.

743
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:24,950
There are so many kids.

744
00:22:26,350 --> 00:22:27,230
Yeah, lots of kids.

745
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:28,800
Well,

746
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:29,590
you're a kid today.

747
00:22:30,590 --> 00:22:31,230
I'm a kid now?

748
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:34,310
So we're doing the mom-and-son thing again?

749
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:37,590
I love coming to amusement parks.

750
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:38,680
Even with my hand hurt.

751
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:39,880
I really enjoy it.

752
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,110
You're such a playful one.

753
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,070
Liu Jiayi.

754
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:44,640
You're impossible to say no to.

755
00:22:47,590 --> 00:22:48,000
Yeah.

756
00:22:54,110 --> 00:22:55,090
What do you want to play?

757
00:22:55,090 --> 00:22:55,710
Liu Jiayi.

758
00:22:56,070 --> 00:22:57,000
Definitely not this one.

759
00:22:57,590 --> 00:22:58,400
Why not?

760
00:22:58,560 --> 00:22:59,400
I'm scared.

761
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:00,710
(Nervous)
I'm scared.

762
00:23:00,710 --> 00:23:01,280
I am scared.

763
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:02,190
Of this one?

764
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,000
(New to me)
For real?

765
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:04,590
Yeah, really.

766
00:23:04,590 --> 00:23:06,070
The drop tower is worse.

767
00:23:06,070 --> 00:23:07,280
But this one's pretty short.

768
00:23:07,710 --> 00:23:08,830
The up and down motion...

769
00:23:09,020 --> 00:23:10,310
(Thinking about it terrifies me.)

770
00:23:10,310 --> 00:23:11,470
I can't stop laughing.

771
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:13,520
I'd rather watch a show.

772
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:14,950
(Fine, your call.)
Here?

773
00:23:14,950 --> 00:23:16,110
There's no show right now.

774
00:23:17,190 --> 00:23:18,640
No show at the moment, sis.

775
00:23:20,830 --> 00:23:21,830
This is driving me crazy.

776
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,590
Can't do much about it.

777
00:23:23,590 --> 00:23:24,920
You're the one who loves it.

778
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:25,310
Guess...

779
00:23:25,310 --> 00:23:26,230
I just love playing it.

780
00:23:26,230 --> 00:23:27,590
...I'll have to spoil you then.

781
00:23:27,590 --> 00:23:28,750
(One word: spoil)
Baby Jiayi.

782
00:23:28,750 --> 00:23:29,760
I love it.

783
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:31,600
The game is about to begin.

784
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,540
Please hold on
to the handrail in front of you.

785
00:23:35,950 --> 00:23:36,640
It's okay.

786
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:38,380
(Yeah, not that great.)

787
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:41,920
Wait.

788
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:42,300
Bro!

789
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:43,190
(This won't end well.)

790
00:23:43,190 --> 00:23:43,950
It's okay.

791
00:23:43,950 --> 00:23:44,830
Wait, bro!

792
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:47,000
Slow down, man!

793
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:55,830
It's fine.

794
00:23:57,830 --> 00:23:58,560
Wasn't that fun?

795
00:23:59,190 --> 00:23:59,880
So much fun.

796
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,710
The best.

797
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:05,520
You silly one.

798
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:09,470
How romantic.

799
00:24:09,470 --> 00:24:10,230
Let's go this way.

800
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,190
You just have to pass by

801
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:18,830
all those food stalls,

802
00:24:18,830 --> 00:24:20,190
so I can smell everything, huh?

803
00:24:21,230 --> 00:24:22,030
Act a little cuter.

804
00:24:22,030 --> 00:24:22,800
I'll buy you some.

805
00:24:25,350 --> 00:24:27,040
I'm the one with money, you know.

806
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:28,190
I'm hungry.

807
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,470
You look like some fluffy white animal.

808
00:24:32,470 --> 00:24:34,160
Like a polar bear or something.

809
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:36,310
Or maybe a Westie.

810
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,400
You look like a bunny.

811
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:39,950
I don't.

812
00:24:41,070 --> 00:24:41,640
Yeah, you don't.

813
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:43,070
Everything you do

814
00:24:43,070 --> 00:24:44,160
is so slow-paced.

815
00:24:44,160 --> 00:24:44,980
You're such a sloth.

816
00:24:58,560 --> 00:24:59,280
So cute.

817
00:24:59,710 --> 00:25:00,920
Super adorable.

818
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:03,830
That's just too cute.

819
00:25:05,900 --> 00:25:06,590
The way it moves.

820
00:25:06,590 --> 00:25:07,580
(Penguin walking)

821
00:25:09,180 --> 00:25:10,580
(Hello)

822
00:25:11,230 --> 00:25:12,710
So adorable!

823
00:25:14,180 --> 00:25:16,190
(I'll wait for you here)
Penguins are the cutest.

824
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,000
Watch your step.

825
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:36,180
(New friends are here)

826
00:25:37,460 --> 00:25:39,540
(We came to feed you!)

827
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,330
Everyone's here.

828
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:45,430
Here comes the squad.

829
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:47,540
(We want some too!)

830
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:49,230
They waddle just like ducks.

831
00:25:49,460 --> 00:25:50,460
(Where are your manners?)

832
00:25:50,460 --> 00:25:51,580
(This scene feels familiar)

833
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:02,000
You really know how to make them compete.

834
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:02,350
No.

835
00:26:02,350 --> 00:26:03,830
I want to give this to the newcomer.

836
00:26:05,190 --> 00:26:06,230
That's so nice.

837
00:26:06,230 --> 00:26:06,760
Yeah, right.

838
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:07,580
I misunderstood you.

839
00:26:07,830 --> 00:26:08,800
Let them play for a bit.

840
00:26:09,040 --> 00:26:09,520
Watch this.

841
00:26:23,110 --> 00:26:24,950
Sweetie, want a bite?

842
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:36,880
See you.

843
00:26:38,590 --> 00:26:39,190
I think

844
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:41,280
everything inside really suits you.

845
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:43,560
You give me that kind of vibe.

846
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:44,830
Like something soft and fuzzy.

847
00:26:44,830 --> 00:26:46,160
You mean I look silly.

848
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:47,070
No, not at all.

849
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,560
(It's a compliment)
You feel so warm.

850
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:50,110
Adorable.

851
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:51,430
Try on this one.

852
00:26:51,880 --> 00:26:52,920
Let me try it on for a sec.

853
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:53,470
I'll help you.

854
00:26:54,590 --> 00:26:55,710
Actually, it's pretty cute.

855
00:26:55,710 --> 00:26:56,110
Good?

856
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:01,230
You seriously can't stop showing off,
can you?

857
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:02,800
I get overwhelmed by it.

858
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:04,490
(Playfully)
I am cool.

859
00:27:04,490 --> 00:27:04,800
Indeed.

860
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:05,680
(Helplessly)

861
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:06,070
Let's go.

862
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,640
I'm craving some food.

863
00:27:12,110 --> 00:27:13,280
Just pretend it cooked it all.

864
00:27:13,580 --> 00:27:15,380
(Promoted to head chef today)

865
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:16,590
It made all the dishes.

866
00:27:17,590 --> 00:27:18,830
Good boy.

867
00:27:19,950 --> 00:27:21,160
So adorable.

868
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,070
Feels like I should've taken

869
00:27:25,070 --> 00:27:26,280
a few more looks at you

870
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:27,560
on the day we first met.

871
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:29,190
Yeah?

872
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:32,310
Things were too chaotic back then.

873
00:27:32,310 --> 00:27:33,230
I didn't...

874
00:27:33,230 --> 00:27:34,730
I sneaked
a few extra glances at you.

875
00:27:34,860 --> 00:27:35,760
(All I can see is you.)

876
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,590
I'll sum it up with one lyric.

877
00:27:37,590 --> 00:27:38,350
A lyric?

878
00:27:38,350 --> 00:27:39,470
You're making it hard for me.

879
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,560
"Just because in that crowd,

880
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:42,920
I looked at you a few more times."

881
00:27:44,350 --> 00:27:45,190
It was you.

882
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:45,950
Yeah.

883
00:27:46,590 --> 00:27:47,310
Me.

884
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:52,230
I only regret one thing.

885
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:54,990
Not giving you all votes on day one.

886
00:27:57,560 --> 00:27:58,160
I think

887
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,590
the rightest thing I did ever was...

888
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,560
After my first day's interview,

889
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:03,590
I saw you were the next.

890
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:05,310
Somehow I felt like

891
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,070
waiting for you.

892
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:07,350
So I waited.

893
00:28:08,230 --> 00:28:09,610
(Night of Day 1)
Why are you here?

894
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,470
Yeah, I just couldn't fall asleep.

895
00:28:11,950 --> 00:28:12,760
Let me walk you out.

896
00:28:13,710 --> 00:28:15,680
You've been staying here till now?

897
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:16,040
Yeah.

898
00:28:18,230 --> 00:28:20,000
I remember seeing you after that interview.

899
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,280
It felt kind of magical to me.

900
00:28:21,710 --> 00:28:22,070
Because...

901
00:28:22,560 --> 00:28:23,590
before you came to me,

902
00:28:23,590 --> 00:28:24,430
I never thought

903
00:28:24,430 --> 00:28:26,040
you actually had any feelings for me.

904
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,470
But back then, did you already know?

905
00:28:27,470 --> 00:28:27,830
Yeah.

906
00:28:27,830 --> 00:28:28,950
I knew at that time.

907
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:31,640
Remember what I said to you

908
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,530
when I walked you home

909
00:28:32,530 --> 00:28:33,400
after that interview?

910
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:34,800
What did you say?

911
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:36,640
I just remember you talked to me a lot.

912
00:28:38,230 --> 00:28:39,160
Right before you left,

913
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:41,710
I told you something.

914
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:43,430
And you answered me.

915
00:28:44,310 --> 00:28:44,760
I said,

916
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:46,920
"If tomorrow there's a chance

917
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:48,880
to choose someone for a date

918
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:49,880
and I choose you,

919
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:50,880
would you choose me too?"

920
00:28:51,470 --> 00:28:52,230
Your answer was,

921
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:52,830
"Probably yes."

922
00:28:55,110 --> 00:28:55,760
But in the end?

923
00:28:56,830 --> 00:28:57,950
The result was

924
00:28:57,950 --> 00:28:58,920
I let myself down.

925
00:28:58,920 --> 00:28:59,880
I didn't win the match.

926
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,230
What I respect most about you is

927
00:29:03,230 --> 00:29:03,640
that

928
00:29:04,430 --> 00:29:06,560
you never tried to stay

929
00:29:07,230 --> 00:29:08,680
by talking your way into it.

930
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:09,160
Never.

931
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:11,280
Like chatting up other girls.

932
00:29:11,830 --> 00:29:12,400
Never once.

933
00:29:14,950 --> 00:29:17,070
And you never seemed worried

934
00:29:17,070 --> 00:29:18,830
or felt the need to explain yourself.

935
00:29:18,830 --> 00:29:19,710
You never asked me

936
00:29:19,710 --> 00:29:20,520
who I'd pick

937
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:21,040
or

938
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:22,470
if I'd vote for you at all.

939
00:29:23,070 --> 00:29:24,640
I've never brought up the voting thing.

940
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:25,590
(I respect your opinion)

941
00:29:25,590 --> 00:29:26,950
Yeah, you never asked me

942
00:29:26,950 --> 00:29:28,520
about my feelings

943
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:29,430
or asked for my votes

944
00:29:29,970 --> 00:29:30,950
cuz you might be leaving.

945
00:29:30,950 --> 00:29:31,430
Or...

946
00:29:31,430 --> 00:29:33,040
You never said anything like that to me.

947
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:34,950
Because to me, it's simple.

948
00:29:34,950 --> 00:29:36,560
I came here just because I wanted to

949
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:37,760
find love.

950
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:39,230
Then I met you,

951
00:29:39,230 --> 00:29:39,920
and I felt like

952
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:41,470
you were the right one.

953
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:44,650
But if you don't like me

954
00:29:44,650 --> 00:29:46,040
and if I leave, I'll still be okay.

955
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:46,920
No regrets.

956
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:47,830
At most,

957
00:29:48,310 --> 00:29:51,230
I just feel a little attached to my friends

958
00:29:51,230 --> 00:29:52,400
on this island.

959
00:29:52,950 --> 00:29:54,310
Or I guess I'll miss the feeling

960
00:29:54,310 --> 00:29:55,280
of escaping real life.

961
00:29:55,280 --> 00:29:55,950
That's all.

962
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:57,760
You're amazing.

963
00:29:59,230 --> 00:30:00,640
But every time you go quiet,

964
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:02,040
it hits me right where it matters.

965
00:30:02,040 --> 00:30:02,880
(Right on the point)

966
00:30:02,950 --> 00:30:03,640
Go quiet?

967
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,160
Like, you never ask me about this

968
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:05,950
or about that.

969
00:30:07,950 --> 00:30:09,140
The more you don't talk about

970
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,390
how you're scared of being left out,

971
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:12,470
or about how few

972
00:30:13,190 --> 00:30:14,000
the votes you got,

973
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,280
the more I'd think of you,

974
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:17,070
the whole thing.

975
00:30:18,830 --> 00:30:19,560
You're smart.

976
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:20,880
You too.

977
00:30:29,350 --> 00:30:29,710
Let's go.

978
00:30:31,310 --> 00:30:32,400
Are there fireworks tonight?

979
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:32,800
Yeah.

980
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:33,230
There are.

981
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:36,160
Fireworks are magical, aren't they?

982
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:37,690
I love watching fireworks.

983
00:30:38,470 --> 00:30:39,310
Me too.

984
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:41,560
The clouds are moving.

985
00:30:42,830 --> 00:30:43,760
Drifting with the moon.

986
00:30:43,760 --> 00:30:44,660
They're moving so fast.

987
00:30:47,350 --> 00:30:49,040
I can't wait.

988
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:53,380
(Screaming Carnival)

989
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:54,950
I think it's gonna be awesome.

990
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:12,040
Is that a little bat?

991
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:12,520
Yeah, it is.

992
00:31:12,520 --> 00:31:13,400
A tiny bat.

993
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:14,160
Or a little demon.

994
00:31:22,070 --> 00:31:22,590
Amazing.

995
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:23,190
Pretty.

996
00:31:45,230 --> 00:31:46,190
Coming.

997
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:48,040
We can eat now.

998
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:48,680
Let's go.

999
00:31:49,230 --> 00:31:50,520
I made you some Luosifen.

1000
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:51,230
Really?

1001
00:31:51,230 --> 00:31:51,920
Yeah, really.

1002
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:54,400
These look delicious.

1003
00:31:55,070 --> 00:31:55,680
They do.

1004
00:31:58,160 --> 00:31:58,950
Not a compliment.

1005
00:31:58,950 --> 00:31:59,590
I get it.

1006
00:32:00,590 --> 00:32:01,520
Try a bite.

1007
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:08,310
Tastes great.

1008
00:32:08,310 --> 00:32:09,190
It's getting cold.

1009
00:32:09,950 --> 00:32:10,640
Yeah, it is.

1010
00:32:11,230 --> 00:32:12,290
No need to cool Luosifen.

1011
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,640
Want some extra soup?

1012
00:32:17,310 --> 00:32:18,000
No.

1013
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:19,880
Still delicious.

1014
00:32:21,190 --> 00:32:22,190
It really is.

1015
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:23,800
Woke up and dinner's already ready.

1016
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,230
I love hearing you speak Cantonese,

1017
00:32:27,230 --> 00:32:28,640
though I can't understand it.

1018
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:29,680
Crispy.

1019
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:31,830
Crispy eggs.

1020
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,590
Crispy eggs.

1021
00:32:33,590 --> 00:32:34,280
It means

1022
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:36,950
eggs with golden crispy edges.

1023
00:32:36,950 --> 00:32:38,450
How long did it take you to cook this?

1024
00:32:39,250 --> 00:32:39,790
Half an hour?

1025
00:32:39,790 --> 00:32:40,660
That's quite a while.

1026
00:32:40,830 --> 00:32:41,640
Really?

1027
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:42,310
Right.

1028
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,190
I had to chop this and that.

1029
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:46,110
Then wash all kinds of things.

1030
00:32:46,110 --> 00:32:47,520
Didn't take that long to stir fry.

1031
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:49,190
But the prep work, that's the tough part.

1032
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:50,950
Yeah, cooking can be a real hassle.

1033
00:32:52,230 --> 00:32:54,110
I can make Luosifen and spicy ramen.

1034
00:32:55,310 --> 00:32:56,070
I should've...

1035
00:32:56,070 --> 00:32:56,400
Let me.

1036
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:58,640
(I should get some sleep)
I should've gone to sleep.

1037
00:32:59,590 --> 00:33:01,450
But you promised
you'd make me something tasty.

1038
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:02,950
Right, I did.

1039
00:33:02,950 --> 00:33:04,560
Actually, I promised Jiawei too.

1040
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:05,070
About what?

1041
00:33:05,070 --> 00:33:06,590
(Sleeping)
He can't leave the island.

1042
00:33:06,590 --> 00:33:08,590
I said, I'll cook something nice for you.

1043
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:12,040
Yeah, I told him that too.

1044
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:17,760
Want some more?

1045
00:33:19,310 --> 00:33:20,280
Sure.

1046
00:33:23,070 --> 00:33:24,040
I'm full.

1047
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:25,310
Really?

1048
00:33:26,310 --> 00:33:27,070
You ate so little.

1049
00:33:27,070 --> 00:33:27,680
Yeah, I know.

1050
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:29,280
I've got a tiny appetite.

1051
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:32,070
No wonder.

1052
00:33:32,070 --> 00:33:33,190
That's why you're so slim.

1053
00:33:34,710 --> 00:33:36,260
I prefer to think of myself as gentle.

1054
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,590
Being slim isn't my best quality, okay?

1055
00:33:39,430 --> 00:33:40,640
Do you think you're gentle?

1056
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,590
Not really.

1057
00:33:41,590 --> 00:33:42,160
Yeah.

1058
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:43,880
Done eating?

1059
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:44,710
Let's clean it up.

1060
00:33:45,430 --> 00:33:46,350
Go get some fresh air.

1061
00:33:46,350 --> 00:33:46,760
Sure.

1062
00:33:48,160 --> 00:33:49,000
You clean up.

1063
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:50,520
Come on, you do it.

1064
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:51,190
No, you do it.

1065
00:33:51,190 --> 00:33:51,950
You clean up.

1066
00:33:52,110 --> 00:33:52,800
I can help you

1067
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:53,950
carry the small bowls.

1068
00:33:59,070 --> 00:33:59,950
So stuffed.

1069
00:34:04,350 --> 00:34:05,350
Are we heading out now?

1070
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:06,560
Yeah.

1071
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:08,950
I wanna go over there.

1072
00:34:09,230 --> 00:34:10,670
We can go to the swings.

1073
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:12,600
Let's swing this way.

1074
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:14,360
When I swing out, it feels kinda scary.

1075
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:15,950
Push me from this side.

1076
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:20,870
Use your strength.

1077
00:34:20,870 --> 00:34:22,430
I'm actually a bit scared.

1078
00:34:22,430 --> 00:34:24,150
If this breaks, you'll fly right off.

1079
00:34:25,630 --> 00:34:26,430
No way, it won't.

1080
00:34:28,470 --> 00:34:29,230
This feels so nice.

1081
00:34:29,230 --> 00:34:29,910
Higher?

1082
00:34:29,910 --> 00:34:30,470
Go for it.

1083
00:34:30,910 --> 00:34:31,670
You're crazy.

1084
00:34:37,500 --> 00:34:38,630
You're not scared, but I am.

1085
00:34:38,630 --> 00:34:39,760
Come on and try it yourself.

1086
00:34:40,190 --> 00:34:41,040
It's a lot of fun.

1087
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:44,320
I don't really feel any fear, to be honest.

1088
00:34:44,320 --> 00:34:44,910
Well, I do.

1089
00:34:44,910 --> 00:34:46,280
You won't once you get used to it.

1090
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:47,080
You go first then.

1091
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:49,600
Can you push a bit higher?

1092
00:34:50,080 --> 00:34:51,120
You're too heavy for that.

1093
00:34:58,430 --> 00:34:59,190
It's nice, right?

1094
00:34:59,190 --> 00:35:00,320
Yeah, it really does.

1095
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,600
Can you push a few more times?

1096
00:35:04,670 --> 00:35:05,520
I'm begging you.

1097
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:07,230
Feels like a workout.

1098
00:35:07,230 --> 00:35:08,390
You're running out of energy.

1099
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:10,950
Too tired.

1100
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:13,230
Let's sit on the chair.

1101
00:35:13,230 --> 00:35:13,840
Let's go.

1102
00:35:18,390 --> 00:35:19,190
Feels nice.

1103
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,520
Honestly, it's pretty comfy.

1104
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:26,040
This place is really beautiful.

1105
00:35:26,360 --> 00:35:26,630
Here.

1106
00:35:26,630 --> 00:35:27,360
This island.

1107
00:35:27,950 --> 00:35:29,470
When you first came to this island,

1108
00:35:29,470 --> 00:35:30,630
how did you feel?

1109
00:35:31,080 --> 00:35:32,710
So many people were talking to me.

1110
00:35:32,710 --> 00:35:33,600
Like,

1111
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:34,390
"what's your name?"

1112
00:35:34,390 --> 00:35:35,630
"Hi, Tianyu."

1113
00:35:35,630 --> 00:35:37,320
Honestly, I was really confused then.

1114
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,190
I just smiled awkwardly.

1115
00:35:39,190 --> 00:35:40,000
At that moment, I...

1116
00:35:40,620 --> 00:35:41,430
(Polite)
did this.

1117
00:35:41,430 --> 00:35:43,140
I couldn't process a single thing they said.

1118
00:35:44,320 --> 00:35:45,230
But you looked fine.

1119
00:35:45,230 --> 00:35:46,360
That day, you seemed calm.

1120
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:48,360
Looked calm, but deep down I was...

1121
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:49,150
A total mess inside.

1122
00:35:49,150 --> 00:35:50,150
Exactly.

1123
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,280
So did you ever think about

1124
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:55,840
falling in love here?

1125
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:58,150
I mean, I did

1126
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,230
think about it,

1127
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:01,560
but...

1128
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,390
Not that...

1129
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:03,320
sure?

1130
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,470
You mean certainty?

1131
00:36:04,470 --> 00:36:04,910
Well,

1132
00:36:05,190 --> 00:36:06,230
I kinda

1133
00:36:06,630 --> 00:36:08,840
just couldn't believe
it would happen.

1134
00:36:09,670 --> 00:36:10,080
For real.

1135
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:11,330
This show just

1136
00:36:11,330 --> 00:36:12,560
brought everyone together.

1137
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,520
If it really happens one day,

1138
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:16,560
that would be such a happy thing.

1139
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,760
Do you think you're a chill type?

1140
00:36:21,390 --> 00:36:22,080
What do you mean?

1141
00:36:22,390 --> 00:36:22,800
I mean,

1142
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:24,150
calm and a bit distant.

1143
00:36:24,670 --> 00:36:25,520
Ah, I get it.

1144
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:25,840
Right.

1145
00:36:26,630 --> 00:36:27,320
I'm not.

1146
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:29,120
So you're a passionate person instead?

1147
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:30,150
I'd say so.

1148
00:36:30,150 --> 00:36:30,950
Yeah.

1149
00:36:30,950 --> 00:36:31,520
It's just that

1150
00:36:31,670 --> 00:36:33,560
sometimes I like being on my own.

1151
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:36,000
But you seem like someone who

1152
00:36:36,520 --> 00:36:37,840
doesn't really show

1153
00:36:38,520 --> 00:36:41,280
how much you like someone, or maybe...

1154
00:36:41,950 --> 00:36:43,800
I don't express it that clearly, right?

1155
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,190
For example, on the island,

1156
00:36:45,190 --> 00:36:46,360
everyone can sense

1157
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:47,430
some people's affectoin.

1158
00:36:48,230 --> 00:36:48,710
But,

1159
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:50,560
what exactly catches your interest?

1160
00:36:51,430 --> 00:36:52,080
About you?

1161
00:36:52,910 --> 00:36:54,190
I think you're very...

1162
00:36:54,190 --> 00:36:55,710
straightforward

1163
00:36:55,710 --> 00:36:56,280
and then

1164
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:57,390
a little carefree,

1165
00:36:57,950 --> 00:36:58,840
which feels refreshing.

1166
00:36:59,630 --> 00:37:00,230
For me,

1167
00:37:00,230 --> 00:37:02,150
I can't stand people who drag things out.

1168
00:37:02,430 --> 00:37:04,630
So personality really matters to you.

1169
00:37:05,320 --> 00:37:06,190
It's super important.

1170
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:07,190
The most important thing.

1171
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:08,670
Honestly,

1172
00:37:08,670 --> 00:37:10,630
in my eyes, you're a calm kind of person.

1173
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,670
You don't talk much when you're in a crowd,

1174
00:37:12,670 --> 00:37:13,150
and then...

1175
00:37:13,430 --> 00:37:14,120
that day,

1176
00:37:14,520 --> 00:37:15,320
when we were working

1177
00:37:15,320 --> 00:37:16,950
on that Book of Riddles,

1178
00:37:16,950 --> 00:37:18,430
you ran pretty fast in front of me.

1179
00:37:18,430 --> 00:37:20,150
That was fast, honestly.

1180
00:37:22,150 --> 00:37:23,190
Huang Jiawei, be careful!

1181
00:37:25,150 --> 00:37:26,390
At that moment,

1182
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:28,000
you really had that impulse

1183
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:30,120
and passion that I'm looking for.

1184
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:33,390
Also, Wan was there too.

1185
00:37:33,520 --> 00:37:34,760
And later you came over.

1186
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:35,710
When we were in the car,

1187
00:37:35,710 --> 00:37:37,390
you said you came

1188
00:37:37,390 --> 00:37:39,950
because you were worried I'd feel bad.

1189
00:37:40,190 --> 00:37:41,950
I didn't want you to overthink.

1190
00:37:41,950 --> 00:37:44,150
And I did think about how you might feel.

1191
00:37:44,150 --> 00:37:45,150
So I

1192
00:37:45,150 --> 00:37:46,560
tried to do something...

1193
00:37:46,710 --> 00:37:48,000
Something that can make me...

1194
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,430
Feel truly at ease.

1195
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:53,320
But actually, you usually

1196
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:54,520
express yourself quite well.

1197
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:56,080
You seem like someone who's not

1198
00:37:56,670 --> 00:37:58,560
too worried about what others might think.

1199
00:37:59,150 --> 00:38:00,390
Because I really value

1200
00:38:00,910 --> 00:38:02,000
everyone's

1201
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:03,120
own space and world.

1202
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:05,000
When I'm working hard,

1203
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:06,190
she works hard too.

1204
00:38:06,670 --> 00:38:07,360
And then,

1205
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:09,520
I don't like telling her what to do

1206
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:11,760
and I don't want her
controlling me either.

1207
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:12,670
I think when two people

1208
00:38:12,670 --> 00:38:13,810
choose to be together,

1209
00:38:13,810 --> 00:38:15,080
it should come from mutual trust.

1210
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:15,840
Yeah.

1211
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,430
I came across a line recently,

1212
00:38:17,430 --> 00:38:19,120
it said love is

1213
00:38:19,430 --> 00:38:20,760
accepting someone as they are,

1214
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:21,950
not as you wish them to be.

1215
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:22,910
You get it,

1216
00:38:23,710 --> 00:38:24,150
right?

1217
00:38:24,150 --> 00:38:24,760
Yeah.

1218
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:25,470
Exactly.

1219
00:38:25,470 --> 00:38:26,760
All those things I just said.

1220
00:38:27,670 --> 00:38:28,990
Back when I was in a relationship,

1221
00:38:28,990 --> 00:38:30,360
I didn't really get this.

1222
00:38:30,950 --> 00:38:32,150
What were you like before?

1223
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:33,670
Well,

1224
00:38:33,670 --> 00:38:35,150
I cared too much about little thing.

1225
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:36,670
Like, all sorts of things,

1226
00:38:36,670 --> 00:38:38,800
what the other person was doing,

1227
00:38:38,800 --> 00:38:40,190
or why they hadn't texted back.

1228
00:38:40,190 --> 00:38:40,670
You know.

1229
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:43,670
When I focused too much on them,

1230
00:38:43,670 --> 00:38:45,230
I'd lose track of who I was.

1231
00:38:46,910 --> 00:38:48,630
So I think,

1232
00:38:48,630 --> 00:38:50,320
liking someone,

1233
00:38:50,320 --> 00:38:51,950
loving someone... those feelings,

1234
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:54,390
they can't be forced.

1235
00:38:55,710 --> 00:38:56,570
Out of all the dates,

1236
00:38:56,630 --> 00:38:59,040
my favorite one was when we went to that

1237
00:38:59,430 --> 00:39:01,000
place that looked like a yurt.

1238
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:01,760
Why that one?

1239
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:03,800
Because it felt really cozy,

1240
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:05,950
like being at home.

1241
00:39:05,950 --> 00:39:08,080
That fancy western restaurant, though,

1242
00:39:08,080 --> 00:39:09,230
was way too high-end.

1243
00:39:09,630 --> 00:39:10,670
When you barely

1244
00:39:10,670 --> 00:39:11,520
know someone,

1245
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:12,800
it's better to

1246
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:15,150
go somewhere more casual,

1247
00:39:15,630 --> 00:39:16,430
right?

1248
00:39:17,430 --> 00:39:19,560
You're not like anyone I've met before.

1249
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:21,190
What kind of person am I then?

1250
00:39:21,190 --> 00:39:22,040
You know, like you.

1251
00:39:22,180 --> 00:39:23,840
(Scratches head)

1252
00:39:23,840 --> 00:39:25,080
What do you mean?

1253
00:39:26,190 --> 00:39:26,910
Bright, warm.

1254
00:39:27,190 --> 00:39:27,840
Keep going.

1255
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:28,910
I'm curious.

1256
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:31,120
Ugly.

1257
00:39:32,670 --> 00:39:33,430
Whatever,

1258
00:39:33,430 --> 00:39:34,190
you're different.

1259
00:39:34,260 --> 00:39:35,420
Do they have the same spark?

1260
00:39:35,870 --> 00:39:36,950
A different kind of spark.

1261
00:39:36,950 --> 00:39:37,800
Go on, say it.

1262
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:38,600
(Tell me)

1263
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:40,050
Spark is spark.

1264
00:39:40,050 --> 00:39:41,000
But yours is different.

1265
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:41,910
Different how?

1266
00:39:41,910 --> 00:39:42,800
Just different.

1267
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:43,270
Come on.

1268
00:39:43,270 --> 00:39:44,670
Never heard of such a thing.

1269
00:39:44,670 --> 00:39:46,600
Your kind of spark

1270
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:48,560
is not even like the village chief's spark.

1271
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:49,430
You get what I mean?

1272
00:39:51,630 --> 00:39:52,950
I just like the kind where

1273
00:39:53,230 --> 00:39:55,360
the guy's a bit more mature than me.

1274
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:56,280
Two people can connect

1275
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:57,630
in an easy and relaxing way.

1276
00:39:57,630 --> 00:39:59,190
We both have fun together,

1277
00:39:59,190 --> 00:40:00,320
and actually like each other.

1278
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,670
It's that natural attraction.

1279
00:40:01,670 --> 00:40:02,910
Sometimes I even hope that guy

1280
00:40:02,910 --> 00:40:04,230
can, to some extent,

1281
00:40:04,230 --> 00:40:06,280
share some mature advice

1282
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:07,630
or give me real support.

1283
00:40:07,630 --> 00:40:08,430
I just think

1284
00:40:08,430 --> 00:40:09,470
that's what truly makes

1285
00:40:09,470 --> 00:40:10,710
a balanced relationship.

1286
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:13,360
I just don't like

1287
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:14,360
those people who,

1288
00:40:14,710 --> 00:40:15,710
you know,

1289
00:40:15,710 --> 00:40:17,910
don't understand a word you're saying.

1290
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:20,150
It's not just about

1291
00:40:20,150 --> 00:40:22,430
choosing a girlfriend, it's also that I

1292
00:40:23,040 --> 00:40:24,430
choose my friends the same way.

1293
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:26,760
If I find someone who is not...

1294
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:27,910
Over time, I'll just...

1295
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:30,520
I'll slowly walk away.

1296
00:40:37,670 --> 00:40:39,360
Bit by bit, you realize she's pretty naive.

1297
00:40:39,360 --> 00:40:40,760
And then you quietly drift away.

1298
00:40:46,020 --> 00:41:02,980
("Live and Love" Release Schedule)

1299
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,810
(Watch Live and Love with us)
Islanders!

1300
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:07,400
(on Thu. 12 PM.)
Today, we'll play four rounds of games.

1301
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:08,920
Now this is what I call a real game.

1302
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:09,380
(Click)

1303
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:10,480
What was that sound?

1304
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:11,440
Yang's eating something.

1305
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:13,760
Well done.

1306
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:15,440
Why the laugh?

1307
00:41:15,480 --> 00:41:17,360
How am I supposed to eat instant noodles?

1308
00:41:17,360 --> 00:41:18,480
You didn't even clean up.

1309
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:19,880
And you're trying to pin it on me?

1310
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:21,060
(Excuse me?)
I helped you win

1311
00:41:21,060 --> 00:41:22,440
and you're accusing me instead?

1312
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:24,560
Then your analysis is totally off.

1313
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:26,640
You've lost your mind over love again.

1314
00:41:26,640 --> 00:41:27,360
(Shocked)
What?

1315
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:28,340
(Look at me)
Bestie.

1316
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:32,160
That's kinda flirty.

1317
00:41:33,460 --> 00:41:34,560
You look like such a goof.

1318
00:41:34,560 --> 00:41:35,800
I think we've already won.

1319
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:36,880
Why can't you grab it?

1320
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:37,920
(Hurry)
Can you even play?

1321
00:41:38,860 --> 00:41:40,180
(Slides to the ground)
